# Double-Slit Interference + Diffraction

The intensity is:

\[
I(\theta)
= I_0 \cos^2\left(\frac{\pi d}{\lambda} \sin\theta\right)
\left(\frac{\sin\beta}{\beta}\right)^2
\]

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

λ = 500e-9
a = 50e-6
d = 150e-6
L = 1
θ = np.linspace(-0.02, 0.02, 3000)

β = (np.pi * a / λ) * np.sin(θ)
envelope = (np.sin(β)/(β+1e-20))**2

interference = np.cos(np.pi * d / λ * np.sin(θ))**2

I = envelope * interference

plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))
plt.plot(L*np.tan(θ), I)
plt.xlabel("y on screen (m)")
plt.ylabel("Intensity")
plt.title("Double-Slit Interference")
plt.grid()
plt.show()
